 American literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAuthorshipxStudy and teaching. 0aCreative writing (Higher education)zIowaxHistoryy20th century. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Writing / General.2bisacsh1 aBerryman, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyle, T. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassill, R. V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCisneros, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDove, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarjo, Joy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrving, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLowell, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathis, Ayana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'Connor, Flannery, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobinson, Marilynne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShelley, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmiley, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSnodgrass, W. D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwofford, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Dylan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVonnegut, Kurt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Marguerite, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part